  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Patients, adult or child, including the diagnosis of APA was made, after consulting their
        physician
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  clinical existence of a PLA (phlegmon), validated by a senior ENT, usually (but not
             necessarily) following a request by an emergency. The visible appearance to the merits
             throat must justify puncture. Cases will be included whether or not they had consulted
             for a &quot;sore throat&quot; in the 10 days preceding the date of diagnosis

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Neoplastic disease of the throat, scalable Hematologic with tonsillar localization
             History of tonsillectomy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
